{{For|the scholarly journal|Teaching Philosophy}}
{{unreferenced|date=December 2012}}

The '''teaching philosophy''' of a candidate for an academic position is a written statement of the candidate's general personal views on [[teaching]].  [[College]]s and [[university|universities]] that advertise a position whose duties require teaching often require the applicant to submit a teaching philosophy with the application.  The philosophy statement often attempts to express what methods of teaching the candidate practices.

